nd": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "his attributes"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (Msb;) [i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he declared,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "celebrated,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "extolled, the perfection"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "purity,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "absolute glory, of God;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he magnified, celebrated, lauded,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "praised, God, by the mention of his names, saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suboHaAna A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "سُبْحَانَ ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sb~H", "text_ar": "سبّح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[alone], (Mgh, K,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tasobiyHN", "text_ar": "تَسْبِيحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he said"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suboHaAna A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "سُبْحَانَ ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Mgh, K;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sabaHa", "text_ar": "سَبَحَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suboHaAnN", "text_ar": "سُبْحَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (K, TA;) the latter, which is like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$akara", "text_ar": "شَكَرَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ukoraAnN", "text_ar": "شُكْرَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", a dial. var. mentioned by ISd; and no regard should be paid to the saying of Ibn-Ya'eesh and others, that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sbHAn", "text_ar": "سبحان"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is an inf. n. of which the verb is obsolete: accord to El-Mufaddal,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suboHaAnN", "text_ar": "سُبْحَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the inf. n. of ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sabaHa", "text_ar": "سَبَحَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he raised his voice with supplication,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "prayer, and magnification"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "celebration"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "praise"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of God, as when one says"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suboHaAna A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "سُبْحَانَ ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and he cites as an ex.,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "qabaHa A@loA_il`hu wajuwha tagoliba kul~amaA\n                      \n                     \n                        sabaHa AlHajiyju wa kab~aruwA A_iholaAlaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "May God remove far from good,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "prosperity,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "success, the persons"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wujuwha", "text_ar": "وُجُوهَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "here meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nufuwsa", "text_ar": "نُفُوسَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") of the tribe"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of Teghlib, whenever the pilgrims raise their voices with supplication,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aall~`hu A^akobaro", "text_ar": "اَللّٰهُ اَكْبَرْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ejaculating"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lab~ayoka", "text_ar": "لَبَّيْكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (MF, TA.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wanaHonu", "text_ar": "وَنَحْنُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nusab~iHu biHamodika", "text_ar": "نُسَبِّحُ بِحَمْدِكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the Kur ii. 28, is a phrase denotative of state, (Ksh, Bd, Jel,) meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "While we declare thy remoteness from evil"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of every kind"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (Ksh, Bd,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "while we say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suboHaAna", "text_ar": "سُبْحَانَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Jel,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "praising Thee,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ksh,) [or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with the praising of Thee,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e.]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "making the praising of Thee to be an accompaniment,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "adjunct, to our doing that:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ksh, Bd, Jel:) so that we are the more worthy to be appointed thy vice-agents. (Ksh, * Bd, * Jel.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fasab~iHo biA@somi rab~ika AlEaZiymi", "text_ar": "فَسَبِّحْ بِا@سْمِ رَبِّكَ العَظِيمِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the Kur lvi. 73 and last verse, means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Therefore declare thou the remoteness from what is unsuitable to his majesty by mentioning the name of thy Lord,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by mentioning the Lord,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for the pronouncing of the name of a thing is the mentioning of it, [i. e., of the thing itself,]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the great"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "name, or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the great"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "Lord: (Bd:) or it means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "therefore pray thou commencing with,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "uttering, the name of thy Lord"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the great"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "name or Lord]: (Kull p. 211:) [for] ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tasobiyHN", "text_ar": "تَسْبِيحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signfies The act of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "praying."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, Msb.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sab~aHa", "text_ar": "سَبَّحَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He prayed."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, Mgh.) And [particularly]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He performed the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "supererogatory"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "prayer of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the period termed"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlD~uHaY", "text_ar": "الضُّحَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yusab~iHu A@ll~`ha", "text_ar": "يُسَبِّحُ ا@للّٰهَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e. ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yuSal~iY Als~aboHapa", "text_ar": "يُصَلِّى السَّبْحَةَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one performs prayer to God,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "either"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "obligatory"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "supererogatory:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[but generally the latter: (see"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1290}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suboHapN", "text_ar": "سُبْحَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":)] and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yusab~iHu EalaY raAHilatihi", "text_ar": "يُسَبِّحُ عَلَى رَاحِلَتِهِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "performs supererogatory prayer"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upon his camel that he is riding"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Msb.) It is said in the Kur [iii. 36],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wasab~iHo biA@loEa$iY~i waA@loA_ibokaAra", "text_ar": "وَسَبِّحْ بِا@لْعَشِىِّ وَا@لْاـِبْكَارَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And pray thou"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the evening,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the afternoon, and the early morning"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) And it is related of 'Omar,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^an~ahu jalada rajulayoni", "text_ar": "اَنَّهُ جَلَدَ رَجُلَيْنِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sab~aHaA baEoda AlEaSori", "text_ar": "سَبَّحَا بَعْدَ العَصْرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "That he flogged two men"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who prayed"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "after the prescribed time of the afternoon-prayer"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S, TA.) You say also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biyadihi", "text_ar": "بِيَدِهِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yusab~iHu bihaA", "text_ar": "يُسَبِّحُ بِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suboHapN", "text_ar": "سُبْحَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "In his hand is a string of beads by the help of which he repeats the praises of God:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suboHapN", "text_ar": "سُبْحَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", below]. (A, Msb. *) ―         -b3-  Also The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "making an exception, by saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ino $aA='a A@ll~`hu", "text_ar": "اـِنْ شَا=ءَ ا@للّٰهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "If God will"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: because, by so saying, one magnifies God, and acknowledges that one should not will unless God will: and thus is expl. the saying in the Kur [lxviii. 28],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^alamo A^aqulo lakumo lawo laA", "text_ar": "اَلَمْ اَقُلْ لَكُمْ لَوْ لَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tusab~iHuwna", "text_ar": "تُسَبِّحُونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Did I not say to you, Wherefore will ye not make an exception?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "addressed to the owners of a garden, who “ swore that they would certainly cut its fruit when they should be entering upon the time of morning, they not making an exception ”]. (TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "O", "Msb", "TA", "T", "A", "Mgh", "K", "Ksh", "Bd", "Jel"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}